Class NBT

java.lang.Object
me.hapyl.spigotutils.module.nbt.NBT

    • setCompoundValue

      public static <A, T> void setCompoundValue(@Nonnull org.bukkit.persistence.PersistentDataHolder holder, @Nonnull String path, @Nonnull NBTType<A,T> type, @Nonnull T value)
      Sets the compound value for the given path.

      The path must be separated by a dot, where the first value is the compound name, and the second is the value path.

      This method will create the compound if it's not already present.

      Proper usage example: 

           setCompoundValue(holder, "foo.bar", NBTType.INT, 69);
      Parameters:
      holder - - Persistent Data Holder.
      path - - Path, separated by a comma. Where the first value is the compound name, and the second is the value path.
      type - - Type of the value.
      value - - Value to set.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the path is not separated by a dot, or there are more than 2 dots.
